commit.message: Added audio clip switch for seamless music
Integrated audio
Imported menu assets
Set up all debris meshes to work as gameplay objects
Got all weapons and most custom debris working
Added custom particles
Added basics of player death mechanic
Added all colors of second metal shard variant
Added solar panels to gameplay
Wave mechanic is completely implemented
Cleaned up GameManager and Interactable scripts
Wrote basic wave logic for GameManager
Got plasma sword working
Added *very* rough draft of particle effect when debris is hit
Finished second pass on shattering physics
Implemented haptic feedback when hitting debris and refined shattering
Started second pass on shattering with real meshes
Debris can optionally begin to come in at steeper angles each time it's recycled

Debris that the player misses or dodges now gets recycled

It will be spawn with an offset based on which direction it was going when it passed the player and will target them again.
Gave junk a slight variation in where it will target
Junk now orients itself and begins moving towards player
Set up pooling for space junk and random spawning at the start of a level
Bounding box for level
Created a cleaned up version of the test scene to begin working on deeper gameplay mechanics
Pieces of shattered objects now activate their own colliders after a brief delay to be allowed to separate
Prototyped shattering
Started building out custom behavior for interactable objects
Implemented grab and release of scene objects
Controlled are now fully mapped to gloves in scene
Set up SteamVR with Rift and implemented a day/night cycle effect
